{
  "texts": [
    "By analyzing these metrics, researchers and practitioners can evaluate whether the algorithm exhibits disparities or biases in its predictions across different groups.",
    "The purpose of a group fairness indicator is to provide an objective measure of fairness and enable the identification of any unfairness or discriminatory patterns in the decision-making process.",
    "In addition, it helps stakeholders assess the performance of algorithms and make informed decisions to mitigate any observed disparities [45].",
    "• Proximity: The definition of proximity is required for exploring CFs.",
    "It refers to the similarity between the original instance and the counterfactual instance generated to explain the prediction of a machine learning model."
  ]
}